<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Moan1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Moan,</orth> subst. lamentation: <bibl n="shak. luc 1363" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1363</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 44.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 44, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.71.13" default="NO" valid="yes">71, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.149.8" default="NO" valid="yes">149, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 295" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 295</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 295" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 295</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 3, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 3, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.4.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 4, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.58" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.5.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 5, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.273" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 273</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 27</bibl>. <cit><quote>to make m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 217" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 217</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 3, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.341" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 341</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 158</bibl>. <emph>to make m. to</emph> == to complain to: <cit><quote>I oft delivered from his forfeitures many that have at times made m. to me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 3, 23</bibl></cit>. Plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 831" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 831</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. luc 587" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 587</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 587" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 587</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 587" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 587</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.190" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.90" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 1, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.80" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 80</bibl> (Ff <emph>griefs</emph>). <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 45</bibl>.<lb />Passing into the sense of grief, sorrow: (tears and groans) <cit><quote>poor wasting monuments of lasting --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 798" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 798</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the sad account of forebemoaned m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 30.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 30, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thine being but a moiety of my m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 60</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>grief</emph>). <cit><quote>that bear this mutual heavy load of m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 60</bibl></cit> cf. also <bibl n="shak. pp 379" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 379</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.273" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 273</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>